Privacy Notice
Effective date: 30 January 2023
This privacy notice is for people who use this SilverCloud® by Amwell website and for people who we communicate with for marketing purposes.
We respect your privacy and will treat your data in accordance with the EU General Data Protection Regulation, the Data Protection Act 2018 and other applicable data protection and e-privacy law.
When we collect or use your data, Amwell is the “data controller”, which means we decide how and why your data is processed. Contact details for  Amwell are listed at the bottom of this notice.
There is a separate
privacy statement for people who use the SilverCloud® by Amwell platform and programmes
.
How we collect your personal data
Your data is collected by us in a few ways:
Data you give directly
Data we collect automatically when you use the website
Data about you we get from third parties
What personal data we collect and use
Here is a list of the categories of personal data that are collected and used, with examples.
Contact details
Your name, company, role, email address, telephone number, postal address, etc.
Enquiry data
Type of enquiry, text of enquiry
Data about your preferences, location, use of our website and emails
IP address, unique identifiers, browser type and version, time zone and language, location, pages viewed
Events
Event registration details include first name, surname, email and job title. We may also video record the events for future uses.
Data we do not collect
Children's data
SilverCloud® by Amwell website and marketing activities are intended for use by adults aged 18 years or over and we do not knowingly collect personal data from people under 16 years of age.
Special category data
SilverCloud® by Amwell does not process “special category data” such as health data through its website or its email services.
If you are looking for help and want to use the SilverCloud® programmes, please contact your local mental healthcare provider to see if SilverCloud® or other suitable services are available in your area.
How and why we use your personal data
SilverCloud® by Amwell processes your data for specific purposes and where there is a legal basis.
Enquiries
We use your contact details and enquiry details to respond to your enquiries. If you send a sales enquiry we will add you as a business contact.
Legal basis: contract, legitimate interests
Events
We record event registrations to allow us to manage and run events, ensure we have capacity and share information regarding the event.
Legal basis: legitimate interests
Marketing
We communicate with business contacts (i.e. existing or potential customers) about relevant products or services.
We also collect business contact information from third parties who manage relevant business contact databases. We classify and rate business contacts based on relevant criteria such as business sector, role, and other factors, which can be considered profiling, through statistical and machine learning processes.
We customise the content shown to users of the website based on your preferences, location and use of the website.
We will not sell, distribute or lease your personal data to third parties. We do not directly market to SilverCloud® platform clients or other individuals (i.e. business-to-consumer).
Legal basis: legitimate interests
Understanding usage and improving services
SilverCloud® by Amwell records data and uses analytics tools to help analyse how users use the site.
Legal basis: legitimate interests
Call recording
With your consent, we may record sales and customer success calls, to reduce the need for note-taking, allow for better follow up and for coaching of employees. We will link call recordings and transcripts with your business contact details.
Legal basis: consent
Legal basis
This explains the legal bases mentioned above
Consent
We get your permission before processing your personal data, in some cases.
Contract
Processing your data is necessary to fulfil a contract or before entering a contract.
Legitimate interests
Processing your data is necessary for our legitimate interests or the legitimate interests of a third party, provided those interests are not outweighed by your rights and interests. Our legitimate interests include:
Communicating in response to enquiries
Communicating relevant information to existing or potential business customers
Understanding the interests and needs of our website users
Maintaining the performance and security of our website and other services
These interests may be overridden by your rights and interests.
Your choices
Cookies
This website uses cookies. You can view our
Cookie Declaration page
for details. You can find information on how to
use browser settings to stop unwanted cookies here
.
You can at any time change or withdraw your consent from the
Cookie Declaration page
on our website.
Marketing
You can opt out from marketing by emailing
enquiries@silvercloudhealth.com,
by using the unsubscribe links in any marketing emails you have received or by
unsubscribing here
.
Your Rights
You have rights regarding your personal data. If you have any questions please contact dataprotection@silvercloudhealth.com
Right to information about processing of your personal details
The aim of this privacy statement is to give you this information.
Right to access your personal data
You have the right to know if your personal data is being held, what categories of data are held, and to receive a copy of all data about you.
Right to change or remove your details
You have the right to correct any inaccurate data, or remove data if it is not necessary for us to hold it.
Right to object to processing
You can object to processing for direct marketing (opt-out), or if it could otherwise affect your rights, freedoms or interests.
Right to data portability
While we do not process your data on the basis of consent, we will provide your data in a portable format.
Right to lodge a complaint
You also have the right to lodge a complaint with a supervisory authority, although we encourage you to contact SilverCloud® by Amwell first.
Contact details for the Data Protection Commission can be found at
https://www.dataprotection.ie
Right to withdraw consent:
where we process your data on the basis of consent, you have a right to withdraw your consent.
You may have also heard about the following rights, however we believe they are not relevant to SilverCloud® by Amwell use of your data.
Rights in relation to automated decision making:
we do not use automated decision making with legal or other significant effects.
